{
  "texts": [
    "Based on the literature, the process only needs to label the event type but does not need to label all event elements in the corpus, which reduces the workload required to create a corpus.",
    "Table V summarizes the main works of pattern-based event extraction.",
    "A previous study (Roman, 2000) constructs a seed pattern set, divides the unlabelled corpus into related text sets and unrelated text sets [45].",
    "It then explores the relevant patterns of related text sets to learn new models incrementally.",
    "Although this method (Roman, 2000) does not require artificial corpus labelling, the pre-classification labelling and seed pattern set they introduce are still relatively heavy."
  ]
}